DropAlert is a machine learning project that predicts whether a student will drop out, remain enrolled, or graduate, using academic, financial, and demographic data.
The pipeline includes:
Data preprocessing: cleaning, encoding, and balancing the dataset with SMOTE
Modeling: training and evaluating an XGBoost classifier
Performance: achieved 86% accuracy and 0.78 F1-score on imbalanced data
Goal: help institutions identify at-risk students early to improve retention
